<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n32054d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n32" href="#n32054d">N32 (VI.B.23)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n32all.htm#n32054d"> 54(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> lieutenant</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[Hindostani]</font> was the natural language of the people in the neighbourhood of Dehli, who formed the bulk of those who resorted to the bazaar, and hence it became the bazaar language. From here it became the <i>lingua franca</i> of the Mogul camp and was carried everywhere in India by the <mark>lieutenants</mark> of the Empire. It has several recognised varieties, amongst which we may mention Dakhini, Urdu, Rekta and Hindi. <small> &ldquo;HINDOSTANI&rdquo; <a name="EBHI" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#EBHI"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) 479(b) [Hindostani as a Lingua Franca]</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
